CHANGELOG.md:53:- Added depth-2 production course helpers (frac-0014): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/production_course.py` now exposes frozen `CourseSummary`, `ChapterDigest`, `ArcPhaseSnapshot`, and `CourseArcPlan` dataclasses plus pure helpers `summarize_course`, `chapter_digest`, `catalog_digest`, `arc_phase_snapshot`, `arc_phase_snapshots`, `course_titles`, `plan_course_arc`, and `validate_course` so runtime diagnostics and tests can render an operator-readable view of a section course (chapter count, transition type, mix role, resolved concept titles in declared chapter order), digest each chapter with its first three sample concept values, snapshot every required arc phase with a `sparse` / `balanced` / `dense` density bucket, plan an arc end-to-end by reusing `course_for_section` across a sequence of section descriptors with the last transition cleanly resolving to `terminal`, and report unknown-value chapters as a sorted tuple. Existing `REQUIRED_CHAPTER_IDS`, `REQUIRED_PHASE_NAMES`, `COURSE_CHAPTERS`, `ARC_PHASE_PROFILES`, `load_course_chapters`, `load_arc_phase_profiles`, `course_chapter`, `course_concept`, `arc_phase_profile`, `transition_type_for_section`, and `course_for_section` semantics are preserved so the score-tree composer and `tests/test_production_course_knowledge_base.py` / `tests/test_production_course_integration.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_production_course_depth.py` pins summary title order, chapter digest metadata + `KeyError` on unknown ids, catalog digest coverage, density bucketing + `KeyError` on unknown phase, end-to-end arc plan + empty short-circuit, and validator behavior, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:55:- Added depth-2 phrase tracker helpers (frac-0013): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/phrase_tracker.py` now exposes frozen `PhraseBoundary` / `PhraseStreamSummary` dataclasses plus `track_phrase_boundaries`, `summarize_phrase_stream`, and `phrase_status_snapshot` so listener tick streams can produce stable typed boundary records, completed-phrase counts, total/longest durations, and listener-shaped status snapshots while preserving the existing `PhraseTracker.update()` event contract used by MIDI, Theramini, and phrase capture runtime paths. `tests/test_phrase_tracker_depth.py` pins the new stream helpers and fractal depth, while existing tracker, capture, listener, and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:57:- Added depth-2 genre literacy helpers (frac-0012): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/genre_literacy.py` now exposes frozen `GenreSummary` / `GenreBlend` dataclasses plus pure helpers `summarize_strategy`, `genre_compatibility`, `blend_genre_strategies`, and `recommend_genre_sequence` so cast-planner, mix, and operator-diagnostics callers can render a stable per-genre summary (label, tempo range, texture density, chromatic tolerance, voice count, dominant grooves, top arc phases, calm/balanced/intense mood bucket), score a bounded `[0.0, 1.0]` symmetric compatibility between two traditions from arc-affinity cosine, modal/groove Jaccard ratios, and texture/chromatic distance, blend numeric hints with a clamped `[0.0, 1.0]` weight (tempo range, texture density, chromatic tolerance, rubato tolerance, repetition tolerance, spatial width, sorted shared modal preferences), and plan one genre per supplied arc phase with rolling fatigue from prior selections. Existing `GenreStrategy`/`REQUIRED_GENRES` data, `strategy_for_genre`, `all_strategies`, `genre_arc_affinity`, `best_genres_for_phase`, and `select_genre` semantics are preserved; `tests/test_genre_literacy_depth.py` pins summary stability and mood bucketing, compatibility self-identity / symmetry / boundedness with related-vs-contrasted ranking, blend interpolation / clamp / modal intersection, sequence per-phase coverage with no immediate repeats, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:59:- Added depth-2 local generation backend behavior (frac-0011): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/client_local.py` now turns `LocalAdaClient` from a disabled stub into a deterministic stdlib-only WAV preview backend. Typed `GenerationRequest` inputs return a real `GenerationResult`, legacy mapping inputs return a queue/cache/storage-friendly payload with `audio_path`, `duration_actual_sec`, `model_used`, `cost_usd=0.0`, latency, and request IDs, and new `local_request_id` / `local_request_summary` helpers expose stable local metadata. `tests/test_client_local_depth.py` pins meaningful summaries, typed WAV output, mapping end-to-end payload shape, deterministic repeat generation, and fractal depth >= 2; existing protocol, Replicate, Modal, local-client, and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:61:- Added depth-2 generation client_protocol helpers (frac-0010): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/client_protocol.py` now exposes a frozen `GenerationOutcome` dataclass plus pure helpers `cost_per_second`, `result_summary`, `format_result_log_line`, and `validate_generation_result` so any backend (Replicate, Modal, local Ada, fakes) can compute USD-per-second cost from a `GenerationResult`, render a stable operator-readable summary dict (rounded duration / cost / per-second cost), emit a single-line `model=… dur=…s cost=$… latency=…ms id=…` log entry with `<unknown>` substituted for an empty `api_request_id`, and validate a result against its `GenerationRequest` (model match, sample-rate floor, duration tolerance, non-negative cost, non-negative latency) into a typed pass/fail outcome with stable reason ordering. The existing `GenerationResult` field order, `GenerationClient` Protocol contract, and downstream `client_replicate` / `client_modal` / `client_local` paths are preserved; `tests/test_generation_client_protocol_depth.py` pins outcome shape, zero-duration cost handling, summary rounding, log-line ID fallback, and accumulated validation reasons, while existing client protocol, Replicate retry, Modal, local-Ada, and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:63:- Added depth-2 counterpoint rule assessment helpers (frac-0009): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/counterpoint_rules.py` now exposes `MotionProfile`, `CounterpointFit`, `motion_profile`, `score_counterpoint_fit`, `rank_counterpoint_rules`, `recommend_counterpoint_rule`, and `counterpoint_pair_summary` so callers can turn a concrete two-voice MIDI pair into motion counts, preferred-interval rate, leap-safety rate, dissonance resolution quality, a bounded rule-fit score, and a stable diagnostics dictionary. Existing registry lookup, dissonance reports, and tracker metadata wiring are preserved; `tests/test_counterpoint_rules_depth.py` pins the new one-path recommendation surface while the existing counterpoint and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:65:- Added depth-2 commission context helpers (frac-0008): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/commission_context.py` now exposes a frozen `CommissionInputs` dataclass plus pure helpers `attention_pressure_from_world`, `commission_inputs_from_tracker_plan`, and `summarize_commission_context` so duet-composer / score-tree callers can resolve the full set of inputs `commission_piece` consumes (cadence, occupancy, day/weekly phase, attention score, narrative pressure, song number, hour) and render an operator-readable diagnostic snapshot without re-deriving the `getattr` plumbing inline. `attention_pressure_from_world` clamps `attention_score` and `experimentation_bias` into `[0.0, 1.0]` and treats `None` / non-numeric inputs as `0.0`; `summarize_commission_context` buckets attention into `low` (<0.33) / `moderate` (<0.66) / `high` and rounds narrative pressure to three decimals so log lines stay stable across small sensor jitters. The existing `commission_context_from_tracker_plan(tracker_plan, world)` keyword-only signature and `(day_phase, weekly_phase)` return contract are preserved (now walking sources with whitespace stripping and only defaulting `day_phase` to `"day"`), so `duet_composer._build_score_tree_piece` and `tests/test_commission_context.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_commission_context_depth.py` pins tracker→world→default fallback, unit-interval clamping, malformed-input handling, full-bundle population, default-occupancy fallback, and the snapshot's bucketed attention plus rounded pressure shape, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors for `bootstrap_identity()` ordering.
CHANGELOG.md:75:- Added depth-2 generation worker helpers (frac-0003): `my-claw/tools/generation_worker.py` now exposes a typed `WorkerConfig`, `load_worker_config`, and `worker_runtime_summary` so callers can resolve and inspect queue/cache/sample/budget/status paths without starting the async worker. `build_queue` accepts an explicit config while preserving env-backed defaults, the signal fallback no longer trips the fractal scanner, and regression coverage pins config resolution, secret redaction, explicit queue construction, worker signal/status behavior, fractal depth, and startup identity persistence anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:79:- Added a stdlib-only narrative API smoke CLI (T-016@20260502T001347Za): `scripts/smoke_narrative.py` reads the base URL from `--base-url` or `NARRATIVE_BASE_URL` (defaulting to `http://cypherclaw:8765`), performs `GET /health` against `cypherclaw.narrative_api`, prints status code plus a 200-char body preview, and exits non-zero on any non-2xx response or connection failure. The optional `--token` flag is sent as the `X-Narrative-Auth` shared-secret header that the API enforces when `NARRATIVE_AUTH_TOKEN` is set, so the Deniable operator can validate the service from their Mac over Tailscale without a virtualenv. Documented in `README.md`; regression coverage in `tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py` pins the success path, non-2xx exit, unreachable-host exit, header propagation, and body truncation.
CHANGELOG.md:89:- Added the CypherClaw narrative API regression suite plus a minimal auth gate (T-005@20260502T001347Z): `cypherclaw.narrative_api.create_app(...)` now accepts an optional `auth_token` keyword that, when set, requires every endpoint to carry a matching `X-Narrative-Auth` header (missing/wrong → 401); empty/unset preserves the existing auth-disabled behavior so T-010's env-var pull and startup warning land cleanly. `tests/test_narrative_api_memory.py` and `tests/test_narrative_api_events.py` now pin the four scenario floors (success path, auth failure when enabled, bad input validation, downstream-engine error handling) for `POST /memory/search`, `GET /events`, and `POST /events`, plus 503 fallback behavior when the deploy-side `cypherclaw.narrative.{memory,events}` package is absent and append-returns-None record synthesis. `pytest --cov=cypherclaw.narrative_api` reports 84% module coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:101:- Added a steady-state SDP cost extractor and committed CSV (T-032@b): `promptclaw/sdp_cost.py` exposes `TOKEN_PRICING`, `match_pricing`, `call_cost_usd`, `DailyCostRow`, `extract_steady_state_cost`, and `write_csv`, applying the substring-matched pricing table from `sdp/telemetry/cost-model.md` (claude-opus-4 $15/$75, claude-sonnet-4 $3/$15, claude-haiku $0.80/$4, gpt-4o $2.50/$10, o3 $10/$40, codex-mini $1.50/$6, fallback $3/$15) to per-task `lead_profile_id` rows in the `.sdp/state.db` `telemetry` table. The CLI `python -m promptclaw.sdp_cost --db .sdp/state.db --days 7 --out sdp/telemetry/steady-state-cost.csv` rolls the 7 most recent active UTC days into the committed `sdp/telemetry/steady-state-cost.csv` (header `date,runs,input_tokens,output_tokens,cache_creation_tokens,cache_read_tokens,total_cost_usd,models`); `cache_creation_tokens`, `cache_read_tokens`, and `thinking_tokens` are reported but not billed, matching the cost-model.md formula. Test coverage in `tests/test_sdp_cost_extractor.py` pins the pricing table values, substring-and-fallback matching, the cost-model.md worked example (`(in/1e6*in_p)+(out/1e6*out_p)`), per-day grouping with sorted unique tier lists, the locked CSV header schema with 4-decimal USD formatting and `|`-joined models, and the CLI's stdout path echo.
CHANGELOG.md:105:- Added a weekly KL-divergence audit between the current IDyOM long-term model and an immutable week-0 snapshot (T-031): new `senseweave.generation.health.idyom_kl_divergence_audit()` returns an `AuditReport` carrying the current `kl_divergence`, `generated_ratio`, `clap_centroid_variance`, and a rolling 8-week `history` of `AuditEntry` records persisted via atomic `os.replace` at `/home/user/cypherclaw-data/state/idyom_kl_audit.json`. KL is symmetric (`0.5*(KL(P||Q)+KL(Q||P))`) over a Laplace-smoothed (`alpha=1.0`) distribution across a fixed test set of melodic n-grams plus an "other" mass bucket. Collapse-drift is flagged only when KL slope is positive AND latest `generated_ratio >= 0.5` AND CLAP-centroid-variance slope is negative across the visible history (≥3 points required); on flag, writes `/tmp/generation_collapse_alert.json` and never auto-rollbacks the LTM. Ships with `my-claw/systemd/cypherclaw-idyom-kl-audit.{service,timer}` (`OnCalendar=weekly`, `Persistent=true`) for weekly invocation; the service sets `PYTHONPATH=/home/user/cypherclaw/tools` so `python3 -m senseweave.generation.health` resolves and points `IDYOM_KL_AUDIT_CONFIG` at a JSON config alongside the new `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/idyom_kl_audit_config.json.example` template that documents the required `current_ltm_path`, `snapshot_path`, `test_ngrams`, `generated_ratio`, and `clap_centroid_variance` fields plus the optional `history_path` / `alert_path` overrides. Test coverage in `tests/test_generation_health.py` pins KL-zero for identical LTMs, KL-positive for divergent LTMs, missing-file behavior, the 8-entry rolling cap, the three-signal conjunction, that two-of-three never flags, alert-file payload shape, file-immutability (no rollback), and the insufficient-history short-circuit.
CHANGELOG.md:111:- Added a live Replicate smoke test for the generation backend (T-005): `tests/test_generation_live_replicate.py` exercises `ReplicateClient.generate(req)` against the real Replicate API with a fixed prompt and seed, and asserts a >100 KB WAV payload, `cost_usd` inside `[$0.01, $0.50]`, and `latency_ms < 60000`. The test is gated behind both the new `--run-live-replicate` pytest flag (registered in `tests/conftest.py` alongside the existing `--run-live-modal` seam) and a non-empty `REPLICATE_API_TOKEN`, so the default `pytest tests/` run skips it. Documented as ~$0.10 per opted-in run.
CHANGELOG.md:113:- Added a local Ada generation backend stub: `senseweave.generation.client_local.LocalAdaClient` now satisfies the shared `GenerationClient` Protocol shape while raising `NotImplementedError("LocalAdaClient: GPU not yet installed; use Replicate or Modal")` until the local GPU path is installed. Added focused tests and an explicit mypy check for Protocol satisfaction.
CHANGELOG.md:115:- Implemented `ModalClient` satisfying `GenerationClient` Protocol in `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/client_modal.py`, enabling CypherClaw to use Modal serverless for generation (CCG-012). The client computes A10G runtime cost from metadata and gracefully degrades when the `modal` SDK is not installed. Also added protocol parity tests and gated live Modal tests behind `--run-live-modal`.
CHANGELOG.md:129:- Added `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-architecture.md` to fill the gap between the sampler PRD and the musicianship roadmap: it lists the landed sampler components (`sample_capture_daemon.py`, `sample_capture_verify.py`, `sampler_buffers.py`, `sampler_dispatch.py`, `synthesis/sampler_effects.scd`, `render/antipatterns.py`), traces the end-to-end signal flow from JACK input through capture, tagging, `index.sqlite`, dispatch, the `sw_sampler_fx` bus, and the master bus, names both live anti-pattern detectors (`sampler_dominating`, `sampler_silent_quintet_member`), enumerates integration seams (identity, cast planner, mix engine, composer, operator diagnostics), and explicitly flags `SampleLibrary`, `SampleSelector`, `sw_sampler.scd`, and quintet identity convergence as still pending; `tests/test_cypherclaw_sampler_architecture.py` pins the doc's required sections, the referenced file paths, and the live anti-pattern names so future renames or section drops force the doc to update with the code.
CHANGELOG.md:130:- Updated `docs/cypherclaw-musicianship-roadmap.md` to describe the active quintet direction: `sw_bell_warm`, `sw_bowed`, `sw_breath`, `sw_pad`, and the new `sw_sampler` memory voice; the roadmap now separates landed sampler modules (`sample_capture_daemon.py`, `sampler_buffers.py`, `sampler_dispatch.py`, `sampler_effects.scd`, anti-pattern checks) from still-pending identity/library/SynthDef convergence so the documentation matches the tree's real partial-rollout state.
CHANGELOG.md:140:- Added course-driven self-critique and revision targets: `self_critique.py` now maps production-course chapter concepts (mode_scale, harmonic_function, meter_groove, counterpoint_relation, synthesis_architecture, mix_role, spatial_intent, genre_strategy, transition_type, phase_profile) to concrete ear-engine metric thresholds via `COURSE_METRIC_MAP`; `thresholds_for_course()` merges per-section course metadata into quality thresholds (stricter wins); `critique_score_with_course()` returns a `CourseCritiqueReport` with `CourseFailure` attribution naming the specific course concept behind each metric violation; `revision_targets_from_failures()` maps failures to `RevisionTargets` specifying which musical dimensions (form, harmony, rhythm, register, mix, strategy) are open for bounded revision without changing piece identity; `revise_score()` accepts an optional `course` kwarg; `tracker_compiler.py` and `duet_composer.py` fallback paths now pass section production_course to `revise_score`.
CHANGELOG.md:145:- Added artistic identity portfolio reporting and surface snapshots: new `portfolio_report.py` module provides `derive_portfolio_report()` for comprehensive identity summaries from repertoire metrics, preferred forms/modes, motif counts, practice block coverage with EMSD course codes, growth-state keys, and ear quality averages; and `derive_surface_snapshot()` for face/operator display data (current song title, section caption, practice block, artistic-intent line). Graceful degradation handles empty repertoire, missing fields, corrupt score trees, and absent growth state without hallucinating data.
CHANGELOG.md:148:- Added pre-performance self-critique and bounded revision passes: new `self_critique.py` module provides `preview_score()` for offline metric analysis, `critique_score()` for threshold-based quality gating, and `revise_score()` for one bounded rewrite attempt that preserves piece identity (key, mood, tempo) while improving at least one failed metric.
CHANGELOG.md:150:- Implemented ST1-ST6 of the score-tree songwriting stack end to end: added `piece_commission.py`, `piece_brief.py`, `form_grammar.py`, `score_tree.py`, `recursive_composer.py`, `composition_gate.py`, `tracker_compiler.py`, and `piece_queue.py`; extended `repertoire_memory.py` to store structural score-tree summaries; and rewired `duet_composer.py` so tracker solo mode can commission a piece, build a complete score tree, gate it, compile it into tracker scenes, and precompose the next piece into a small persistent queue instead of treating the tracker as the composer.
CHANGELOG.md:179:- Collapsed split boot ownership for the core AV stack: `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now delegates audio/composer/face/gallery/room-listener/sample startup to `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh`, which keeps one authority for those daemons instead of racing duplicate boot paths.
CHANGELOG.md:184:- Relaxed composer restart verification to the real steady-state condition: `restart_composer.sh` now waits for any healthy `duet_composer.py` process instead of only trusting the very first child PID, which avoids false failures during the current live startup race.
CHANGELOG.md:187:- Tightened the cold-boot wrapper to avoid daemon duplication: it now waits for `SuperCollider:out_1` before launching the meter, and it only backfills `room_listener.py`, `sample_playback_engine.py`, and `face_display.py` if another startup source has not already brought them up during the same boot.
CHANGELOG.md:188:- Made the cold-boot wrapper opportunistic instead of combative: if `scsynth` and `duet_composer.py` are already present from another startup path, `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now skips `start_audio.sh` / `restart_composer.sh` entirely and only backfills the missing meter/listener surface.
CHANGELOG.md:210:- Expanded CypherClaw boot coverage for the EMSD sampler path: `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now starts `theramini_listener.py` and `contact_listener.py` alongside the room listener so the stable sample aliases can refresh during unattended startup instead of remaining planned-but-missing files.
CHANGELOG.md:212:- Wired the next EMSD runtime pass into live state: added `emsd_runtime.py`, taught `duet_composer.py` to build a typed EMSD context per tracker song and publish arc/mix/sample/DSP/identity fields into `/tmp/composer_state.json`, extended `repertoire_memory.py` to retain `patch_name`, and taught `self_listener.py` to publish `/tmp/glyph_audio_features.json` by combining live audio analysis with composer/cadence state for GlyphWeave-facing consumers.
CHANGELOG.md:213:- Built the first end-to-end EMSD package: added a 40-course curriculum catalog plus generated `my-claw/curriculum/EMSD-*` scaffolds, and implemented `sound_palette_lab.py`, `sample_lab.py`, `mix_engine.py`, `procedural_arc.py`, `dsp_scene_lab.py`, `artistic_identity.py`, and `capstone_engine.py` so the electronic music production roadmap now exists as runnable code and tests instead of only a brief.
CHANGELOG.md:265:- Taught Telegram `/prd` to load stage order from `sdp/execution-roadmap.md` and batch mappings from `sdp/execution-roadmap.queue-map.json`, so roadmap output follows the current clone/identity/embodiment/publication plan instead of a stale hardcoded stage list.
CHANGELOG.md:293:- Added Decision Store for Architecture Decision Records (ADRs) with keyword-based retrieval.
